{"article_id":"2smoGvt7Z8i20Acw","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Supporters worry about cascading problems","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"as key provisions go into effect .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"Uncertainty about the law has risen","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"as time has passed","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Four in 10 Americans do n't believe","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"the law is still in place","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"WAS","depth":2},{"id":7,"text":"INGTON --","depth":3},{"id":8,"text":"he Affordable Care Act is sure to survive the latest vote by the House of Representatives Thursday","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"o repeal it","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"since the Senate does n't plan to take it up","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"nd President Obama would veto a repeal bill","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"f it somehow reached his desk -","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"ut the administration 's signature legislative achievement still faces serious perils ahead .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"mericans have a dimmer view of the health care law now","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"han they did","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"hen Obama triumphantly signed it three years ago ,","depth":13},{"id":17,"text":"ccording to monthly tracking polls by the Kaiser Family Foundation .","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"he public 's divided view and relentless Republican attacks have made it easier for governors and state legislators to balk at cooperating with the law .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"t is designed to provide coverage for millions of Americans","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"ho have n't qualified for Medicaid in the past","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"nd do n't get insurance through their employers .","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"hat could have a cascading effect :","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"esistance by the states will make it harder for the law to work","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"s promised","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"hen Medicaid expands next year","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"nd the health-insurance marketplaces","depth":15},{"id":27,"text":"here the uninsured can shop for plans","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"pen this fall .","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"hat could fortify the arguments of those","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"ho warned","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"he law was a mistake from the start","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"nd threaten fundamental provisions of it down the road .","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"` For most of the Obama administration , the thought was the bill was passed","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"nd it 's over , ''","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"ays Robert Blendon , a Harvard professor and influential analyst","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"ho supports the law .","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"he president understandably turned his attention to the fragile economy ,","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"nd the most far-reaching expansions of coverage were delayed until 2014","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"leaving the door open for opponents","depth":15},{"id":40,"text":"o warn of calamity ahead .","depth":15},{"id":41,"text":"` By the time they returned to it , ''","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"lendon says of White House officials ,","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"` opinions were really embedded . ''","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"ust over a third of Americans , 35 % , have a favorable opinion of the health law ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"ccording to the Kaiser survey","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"aken last month ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"own from 46 %","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"ho had a positive view","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"hen it was signed in 2010 .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"ow 40 % have an unfavorable opinion","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"precisely the same as three years ago -","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"nd nearly one in four , 24 % , say","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"hey do n't have an opinion .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"he poll of 1,203 adults ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"aken April 15-20 ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"as a margin of error of +/-3 percentage points .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"ncertainty about the law has risen","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"s time has passed ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"nd confusion about what it does and how it works is especially high among those","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"t is designed to help .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"n fact , four in 10 Americans do n't believe","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"he law is still in place ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"aying inaccurately","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"hat it 's been overturned by the Supreme Court","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"r repealed by Congress .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"till the law ?","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"s you know ,","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"health care bill was signed into law in March 2010 .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"hat 's its current status ?","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"oll","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"aken April 15-20 of 1,203 adults .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"argin of error +/- 3 percentage points .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"` People have n't really seen the benefits of it ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"nd it 's had hundreds of millions of dollars in ads","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"ttacking it , ''","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"ays Neera Tanden ,","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"ho helped shape the law as Obama adviser","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"nd now heads the liberal Center for American Progress .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"` One party was definitely consistently criticizing it ,","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"nd Democrats have not been sufficiently defending it .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"o it 's been a lopsided argument . ''","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"he White House is scrambling to bolster support for and knowledge about the law ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"n part to encourage younger and healthier Americans","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"ho lack health insurance","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"o shop for a plan","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"hen the exchanges open Oct. 1 .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"fficials are trying to spotlight popular policies","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"hat already have gone into effect ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"ncluding provisions","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"hat provide free preventive care for seniors","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"nd allow young adults to stay on their parents ' insurance plans .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"hey also are trying to reassure skeptical employers about the law and its provisions .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"n a Gallup Poll last month , owners of small businesses predicted by 5-1 , 48 % -9 % ,","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"hat the Affordable Care Act was going to be bad rather than good for their businesses .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"bout four in 10 said","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"hey had held off plans","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"o hire new workers","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"nd pulled back on plans","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"o grow their businesses","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"ecause of the law and its mandates .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"` The law is here","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"o stay , ''","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"bama declared at an East Room event last week","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"not an assertion","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"residents typically feel compelled to make .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"e noted","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"hat not only did Congress pass the law in 2010","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"albeit without a single Republican vote )","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"ut also the Supreme Court upheld it last year .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"hen voters `` went to the polls","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"nd decided to keep going in this direction ''","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"y re-electing him last November .","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"` With something as personal as health care , I realize","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"here are people","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"ho are anxious ,","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"eople","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"ho are nervous ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"aking sure","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"hat we get this done right , ''","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"he president said .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"` I 'm here","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"o tell you ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"am 110 % committed to getting it done right .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"t 's not an easy undertaking ,","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"ut if it were easy ,","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"t would have already been done a long time ago .","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"ndoubtedly , there will be some mistakes and hiccups","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"s the thing get started up ,","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"ut we 're learning already from them . ''","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"mong those most anxious and nervous about possible `` mistakes and hiccups '' ahead are Democratic members of Congress","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"ho voted for the law .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"pposition to Obamacare fueled the rise of the Tea Party and the Republican takeover of the House in the 2010 congressional elections .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"` Those of us","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"ho remember 2009 and the town-hall meetings ,","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"e want to be fully prepared now , ''","depth":14},{"id":136,"text":"ays Rep. Jan Schakowsky , D-Ill. ,","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"ecalling raucous meetings with constituents","depth":15},{"id":138,"text":"ho saw the health care plan as an expensive and dangerous government overreach .","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"` People are concerned","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"hat we do some better messaging before the August recess . ''","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"he and other congressional Democrats met last week with Ron Pollack , head of Families USA , a leading backer of the law .","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"` People are very much wanting to make sure","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"he implementation goes as smoothly as possible , ''","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"ollack says .","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"` In 2009 and 2010 , congressional Democrats played rope-a-dope","depth":15},{"id":146,"text":"nd they got hurt . ''","depth":15},{"id":147,"text":"his time ,","depth":16},{"id":148,"text":"e advised ,","depth":16},{"id":149,"text":"hey should be prepared to detail the law 's benefits and rebut any `` false claims '' about it .","depth":15},{"id":150,"text":"eanwhile , Republicans relish the idea","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"f brandishing Obamacare as a political weapon in the midterms .","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"ouse Speaker John Boehner says","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"he House brought up overall repeal of the law for the third time","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"ince it was enacted","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"imply to give Republican freshmen a chance","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"o stand against it .","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"` We 've got 70 new members","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"ho have not had an opportunity","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"o vote on the president 's health care law , ''","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"e told reporters beforehand .","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"oehner 's office says","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"t is the 37th vote in the House","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"n repealing , curtailing or defunding all or part of the Affordable Care Act .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"epublicans have failed to repeal the law in its entirety","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"ut seven bills","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"evising particular provisions","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"ave been enacted .","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"he GOP also has denied funding requests by the Department of Health and Human Services","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"o help implement the law ,","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"ncluding the campaign","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"o boost participation in the insurance exchanges .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"hat 's particularly important","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"ecause","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"f only people with chronic conditions and higher medical bills sign up ,","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"remiums would soar","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"nd the underpinnings of the system would be undercut .","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"hile the law mandates","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"hat most of the uninsured get insurance ,","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"he annual penalty","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"or failing to do so","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"s low enough","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"$ 95 in 2014 ,","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"ising to $ 695 in 2016 )","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"hat some people simply will choose to pay it .","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"ews reports","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"hat HHS Secretary Kathleen Sebelius has been raising private money for the effort","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"parked objections and demands for information this week from Republican lawmakers .","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"ennessee Sen. Lamar Alexander , the top Republican on the Senate Health committee , says","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"e will formally request an investigation by the congressional General Accounting Office this week ,","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"omparing her actions to the Iran-contra scandal in the Reagan administration .","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"ince March , Sebelius has made fundraising calls on behalf of Enroll America to the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation and H & R Block ,","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"ccording to her spokesman , Jason Young .","depth":13},{"id":194,"text":"nroll America , a non-profit organization","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"reated","depth":15},{"id":196,"text":"o encourage the uninsured Americans to sign up for the exchanges ,","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"s headed by Anne Filipic , a former aide to Obama and Sebelius","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"ho worked in the White House","depth":15},{"id":199,"text":"efore resigning","depth":16},{"id":200,"text":"o lead the group .","depth":16},{"id":201,"text":"ebelius also made more public appeals to charitable groups , insurers , pharmaceutical companies and others","depth":14},{"id":202,"text":"o help the enrollment effort .","depth":14},{"id":203,"text":"oung says","depth":14},{"id":204,"text":"ebelius ' fundraising efforts were permitted under provisions","depth":16},{"id":205,"text":"hat date to 1976 in the Public Health Service Act ,","depth":16},{"id":206,"text":"hich allows the HHS secretary to encourage support for non-profit groups","depth":16},{"id":207,"text":"hat promote public health .","depth":16},{"id":208,"text":"e said","depth":13},{"id":209,"text":"er predecessors made similar appeals","depth":14},{"id":210,"text":"hen other new federal programs were launched ,","depth":15},{"id":211,"text":"ncluding the Medicare prescription drug benefit during the Bush administration and the children 's health insurance program during the Clinton years .","depth":15},{"id":212,"text":"lexander is not persuaded .","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"` I do n't see how that 's different from what Oliver North did at the end of the Reagan administration","depth":13},{"id":214,"text":"o raise money privately","depth":14},{"id":215,"text":"nd use it","depth":15},{"id":216,"text":"o support the contra rebels '' in Nicaragua ,","depth":15},{"id":217,"text":"e said in an interview . `` A joint select committee of Congress","depth":15},{"id":218,"text":"hat was bipartisan","depth":15},{"id":219,"text":"aid","depth":14},{"id":220,"text":"he principle problem with Iran-contra is that the Reagan administration was using private funds and private entities","depth":14},{"id":221,"text":"o do something","depth":15},{"id":222,"text":"hat Congress had refused to do . ''","depth":15},{"id":223,"text":"e said","depth":12},{"id":224,"text":"hat Sebelius may be violating the Constitution and the Anti-deficiency Act ,","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"hich prohibits federal employees from spending money beyond that","depth":14},{"id":226,"text":"uthorized by law .","depth":14},{"id":227,"text":"he Affordable Care Act envisioned most states","depth":10},{"id":228,"text":"stablishing and running their own insurance exchanges .","depth":10},{"id":229,"text":"ut only 17 states and the District of Columbia are moving ahead with plans","depth":12},{"id":230,"text":"o do that ;","depth":12},{"id":231,"text":"nother seven are setting up `` partnership exchanges '' with the federal government .","depth":11},{"id":232,"text":"ut 26 states ,","depth":12},{"id":233,"text":"ncluding six of the 10 most populous ones ,","depth":12},{"id":234,"text":"re leaving the job entirely to the federal government .","depth":11},{"id":235,"text":"he administration says","depth":10},{"id":236,"text":"ne-third of the prime target group nationwide","depth":12},{"id":237,"text":"healthy 18- to 34-year-olds","depth":13},{"id":238,"text":"ho do n't have insurance -","depth":13},{"id":239,"text":"ive in California , Florida and Texas .","depth":11},{"id":240,"text":"f that trio of states , only California is setting up a state exchange .","depth":9},{"id":241,"text":"he other major part of the Affordable Care Act","depth":13},{"id":242,"text":"o cover the uninsured ,","depth":13},{"id":243,"text":"xpanding Medicaid","depth":13},{"id":244,"text":"o include more low-income Americans ,","depth":13},{"id":245,"text":"s opposed by at least 20 governors ,","depth":12},{"id":246,"text":"ccording to the Kaiser foundation .","depth":12},{"id":247,"text":"he Supreme Court ruling last year upheld the law 's controversial individual mandate","depth":11},{"id":248,"text":"ut gave states the option","depth":12},{"id":249,"text":"f choosing not to participate in the Medicaid expansion .","depth":12},{"id":250,"text":"n the states","depth":11},{"id":251,"text":"hat do n't ,","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"he uninsured","depth":12},{"id":253,"text":"ho are too poor","depth":13},{"id":254,"text":"o afford to buy coverage in the exchanges , even with a federal subsidy ,","depth":13},{"id":255,"text":"re out of luck .","depth":11},{"id":256,"text":"emocratic pollster Mark Mellman says","depth":11},{"id":257,"text":"he public still could be won over to embrace the law .","depth":11},{"id":258,"text":"` It 's slightly more unpopular than popular ,","depth":13},{"id":259,"text":"ut it 's not radioactive , ''","depth":13},{"id":260,"text":"e says ,","depth":12},{"id":261,"text":"espite a concerted and well-funded campaign against it .","depth":11},{"id":262,"text":"n the end , views of the law will depend on whether it works","depth":12},{"id":263,"text":"s promised ,","depth":12},{"id":264,"text":"epublican pollster Bill McInturff agrees .","depth":11},{"id":265,"text":"` If in fact this is a good and affordable product","depth":15},{"id":266,"text":"hat works ,","depth":15},{"id":267,"text":"t will work , ''","depth":14},{"id":268,"text":"e says .","depth":13},{"id":269,"text":"` If what starts to happen is small employers start dumping people into the exchanges","depth":15},{"id":270,"text":"nd they lose good private coverage ;","depth":15},{"id":271,"text":"f healthy people would rather pay the penalty","depth":15},{"id":272,"text":"han sign up -","depth":15},{"id":273,"text":"hen it 's going to immediately turn into a problem with demands","depth":14},{"id":274,"text":"o change it . ''","depth":14},{"id":275,"text":"ver the next year , the health care law is likely to succeed in some states","depth":15},{"id":276,"text":"nd fail in others ,","depth":15},{"id":277,"text":"nalyst Blendon says .","depth":14},{"id":278,"text":"` Best case :","depth":14},{"id":279,"text":"he governor and the legislature support it ,","depth":16},{"id":280,"text":"hey have a state exchange ,","depth":17},{"id":281,"text":"nd what I call the civic leadership is all behind it","depth":18},{"id":282,"text":"the business people , the unions , the religious leaders .","depth":18},{"id":283,"text":"hen the problem is just technically ,","depth":16},{"id":284,"text":"ow do we get this set up","depth":17},{"id":285,"text":"nd how do we get people to understand '' how it works ?","depth":17},{"id":286,"text":"t the other extreme are states","depth":14},{"id":287,"text":"hat are declining to participate in the Medicaid expansion and to put the force of the state government and local leadership behind the new marketplaces .","depth":14},{"id":288,"text":"` If you do n't offer Medicaid","depth":17},{"id":289,"text":"nd you do n't have a lot of support for the federally run exchange ,","depth":17},{"id":290,"text":"t will be incredibly easy for the one-third of people younger and healthier not to enroll , ''","depth":16},{"id":291,"text":"e cautions .","depth":15},{"id":292,"text":"` At least in 20 states , it 's set up","depth":15},{"id":293,"text":"o fail . ''","depth":15}],"relations":[{"parent":587,"left":299,"right":586,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":299,"left":295,"right":298,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":296,"right":297,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":296,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":586,"left":6,"right":585,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":585,"left":7,"right":584,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":584,"left":372,"right":583,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":372,"left":363,"right":371,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":363,"left":334,"right":362,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":334,"l